As of the census<ref name="census2">{{cite web |title=U.S. Census website |url=https://www.census.gov |access-date=23 May 2011 |website=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref> of 2010, there were 483 people living in the CDP. There were 193 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 94.6% White, 0.8% American Indian and Alaska Native, 0.4% Asian, 0.2% Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander, 2.3% from some other race, and 1.7% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 5.2% of the population.
